  <prompt>
    Migrate the `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` playbook node graph in Dataverse from the current single-action Output schema to N Action nodes (one per output section) + 1 `DeliverComposite` Output Node per FR-52 / FR-58. Section assignment uses the playbook's existing output schema sections (parties+direction, definition, exclusions, term+survival, permittedUse, remedies, redFlags â€” or whatever the current production schema declares). Chat sibling `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` STAYS single-action â€” do NOT migrate; verify regression remains green. Migration is via Dataverse update (`scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` or MCP `update_record` on `sprk_playbooknode`/`sprk_configjson`) â€” rewrite the Output Node `sprk_configjson` to `DeliverComposite` and add the new Action nodes wired by `sectionName`. Validate end-to-end against bff-dev: NDA upload â†’ vector match â†’ top-N â†’ user clicks â†’ playbook executes via DeliverComposite path â†’ workspace widget renders per section via `section_data` events.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform Dataverse + playbook engineer. Expert in `sprk_playbook` / `sprk_playbooknode` node graphs, `PlaybookExecutionEngine` Output Node semantics, and FR-52 multi-node composition.</role>

  <goal>
    `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` node graph in Dataverse is rewritten so its single legacy Output Node becomes N Action nodes (one per output section) feeding 1 `DeliverComposite` Output Node keyed by `sectionName`. End-to-end run against bff-dev produces correct per-section streaming (`section_started`, `section_data`, `section_completed` events keyed by section name, NOT schema position) and the workspace widget renders identical output (post-migration schema observable from existing widget MATCHES pre-migration). Chat sibling `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` is untouched and its regression test (FR-26 enriched fields + FR-30 `FieldDelta` streaming) remains green. Playbook lookup cache (ADR-014) invalidated after the data update.
  </goal>

  <context>
