  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read existing `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` node graph in Dataverse (via MCP `read_query` against `sprk_playbook` + `sprk_playbooknode` joined by parent) â€” capture current Output Node `sprk_configjson` + the section names declared in its output schema. Snapshot to `notes/handoffs/118R-pre-migration-snapshot.json` for rollback.</step>
    <step order="2">Read the chat sibling `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` node graph; confirm it is structurally distinct (single-action Output) and document baseline. This is the regression target â€” it MUST be untouched by this migration.</step>
    <step order="3">Inspect the FR-52 `DeliverComposite` node contract from tasks 114b/114c (read `PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs` + the new `DeliverCompositeOutputNode` impl). Confirm the `sectionName`-keyed wiring schema and required `sprk_configjson` shape.</step>
    <step order="4">Design the new node graph for `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`: one Action node per output section (preserving the section names from step 1) feeding one `DeliverComposite` Output Node. Each Action node's prompt template extracts ONE section from the document; the composite node assembles them keyed by `sectionName`.</step>
    <step order="5">Author the migration JSON at `infra/dataverse/playbooks/summarize-document-for-workspace-v1-multinode.json` capturing the new node graph; preserve `sprk_playbookid` (immutable opaque ID) and `sprk_playbookcode = summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` (slug unchanged).</step>
    <step order="6">Apply the migration via `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (or MCP `update_record`/`delete_record`+`create_record` per script semantics) against the DEV environment. Idempotent; do NOT delete the playbook record itself â€” rewrite its child nodes only.</step>
    <step order="7">Invalidate the `PlaybookLookupService` cache (ADR-014) â€” call the cache-flush endpoint or restart the BFF dev instance. Verify next request sees the new node graph via telemetry (node count + section names).</step>
    <step order="8">Add or update integration test `SummarizeDocumentE2ETests.MultinodeWorkspace_NDA_RendersAllSections`: upload NDA via `POST /api/chat/document-upload` â†’ trigger vector match â†’ simulate user click on top-N candidate â†’ assert SSE event sequence shows N `section_started` + N `section_completed` events keyed by section name (NOT schema position).</step>
    <step order="9">Verify chat sibling regression: run existing `SummarizeDocumentE2ETests.ChatSibling_NDA_StreamsFieldDelta` test â€” must remain green; assert FR-26 enriched fields (`PrecomputedSummary`, `Manifest`, `ClassifiedDocType`, `ClassifiedConfidence`, `Sections`) preserved and FR-30 `FieldDelta` events still flow.</step>
    <step order="10">Workspace widget render verification: run the workspace UI flow against bff-dev; visually confirm the migrated playbook produces the same 6-section render as pre-migration (NFR-02 production-bound preservation).</step>
    <step order="11">Measure BFF publish size; report delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB) â€” expect ~0 MB (data-only change).</step>
    <step order="12">code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates). Verify telemetry tier-1 audit shows no leaked section content.</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 118R â†’ âś…; current-task.md â†’ ready for 118a + 118b (parallel).</step>
  </steps>

